<div class="exercise">
<h2>Better variable names</h2>

<p> You are reviewing a friends code, unfortunetly your friend tends to use terrible variable names. Suggest better ones!</p>

<textarea class="codeinput" linecount="15">
# Calculate the area of a circle
x = 1.5
bananas = 3.14 * x**2
print(bananas)

# Calculate the total price the eggs 
number_of_eggs_I_am_planning_to_buy = 13
price_of_a_single_egg_in_store = 0.3
print(number_of_eggs_I_am_planning_to_buy * price_of_a_single_egg_in_store)

# Ask the user for their name
UserName = input("Please, enter your name")
</textarea><br>

<div class="button-row"><button class="run-button" disabled>▶ Run</button> <button class="reset-button">↻</button></div>

<h3>Output:</h3>
<pre class="output"></pre>

<details><summary>Solution</summary>
<p>
One possible solution:
<textarea class="solution">
# Use descriptive names
r = 1.5
area = 3.14 * r**2
print(area)

# Use concise names
num_eggs = 13
price_per_egg = 0.3
print(num_eggs * price_per_egg)

# Python recommends snake_case for variable names, UserName is CamelCase
UserName = input("Please, enter your name")</textarea>
</p>
</details>
</div>


<div class="exercise">
<h2>Sum and mean</h2>

<p> You have three numbers. Print out their sum and their mean.</p>

<textarea class="codeinput" linecount="10">
num1 = 12
num2 = 1
num3 = 29
</textarea><br>

<div class="button-row"><button class="run-button" disabled>▶ Run</button> <button class="reset-button">↻</button></div>

<h3>Output:</h3>
<pre class="output"></pre>

<details><summary>Solution</summary>
<p>
<textarea class="solution">
# Sum
s = num1 + num2 + num3
print(s)

# Mean is the sum divided by the number of samples
m = s/3
print(m)

# Alternatively
print(num1+num2+num3, (num1+num2+num3)/3)</textarea>
</p>
</details>
</div>



<div class="exercise">
<h2>Check splitter</h2>

<p> You went to a schnitzel restaurant with a bunch of your friends. You decided that you will split the check evenly.
Calculate and print out the amount you have to pay.</p>

<textarea class="codeinput" linecount="6">
tip_percentage = 0.10
check_total = 30.5
num_people = 10</textarea><br>

<div class="button-row"><button class="run-button" disabled>▶ Run</button> <button class="reset-button">↻</button></div>

<h3>Output:</h3>
<pre class="output"></pre>

<details><summary>Solution</summary>
<p>
<textarea class="solution">
amount_per_person = (1. + tip_percentage)*check_total / num_people
print(f"You have to pay {amount_per_person:.2f}.")</textarea>
</p>
</details>
</div>


<div class="exercise">
<h2>Fixing the code</h2>

<p> Your friend was asked to write code that asks for two numbers and calculates their difference.
However, their solution does not seem to work. Help fix the problem!</p>

<textarea class="codeinput" linecount="10">
number = float(input("Enter a number"))
number = float(input("Enter a number"))

difference = number - number

print("The difference is", difference)
</textarea><br>

<div class="button-row"><button class="run-button" disabled>▶ Run</button> <button class="reset-button">↻</button></div>

<h3>Output:</h3>
<pre class="output"></pre>

<details><summary>Solution</summary>
<p>
The variable names need to be different, otherwise the second <code>input()</code> overwrites the first.
<textarea class="solution">
number1 = float(input("Enter a number"))
number2 = float(input("Enter a number"))

difference = number1 - number2

print("The difference is", difference)</textarea>
</p>
</details>
</div>


<div class="exercise">
<h2>Years since</h2>

<p> Ask the user what year is it and print out the number of years since the release of Back to the future</p>

<textarea class="codeinput" linecount="6">

</textarea><br>

<div class="button-row"><button class="run-button" disabled>▶ Run</button> <button class="reset-button">↻</button></div>

<h3>Output:</h3>
<pre class="output"></pre>

<details><summary>Solution</summary>
<p>
<textarea class="solution">
year_now = int(input("What year is it?"))

age = year_now - 1985

print("Back to the future was released", age, "year ago.")

# You can also combine printing and computing the age
print("Back to the future was released", year_now-1985, "year ago.")

</textarea>
</p>
</details>
</div>



<div class="exercise">
<h2>Birthday</h2>

<p> This is a candle:</p>
<pre>
()
||
||
</pre>
<p>Print out as many candles in a row as your age.</p>

<textarea class="codeinput" linecount="10">

</textarea><br>

<div class="button-row"><button class="run-button" disabled>▶ Run</button> <button class="reset-button">↻</button></div>

<h3>Output:</h3>
<pre class="output"></pre>

<details><summary>Solution</summary>
<p>
<textarea class="solution">
age = 18
print("() "*age)
print("|| "*age)
print("|| "*age)</textarea>
</p>
</details>
</div>



